{{Infobox language |name = Lemolang |nativename = Limola |states = [[Indonesia]] |region = [[Sulawesi]] |speakers = 2,000 |date = 1991 |ref=e18 |familycolor = Austronesian |fam2 = [[Malayo-Polynesian languages|Malayo-Polynesian]] |fam3 = [[South Sulawesi languages|South Sulawesi]] |fam4 = |iso3 = ley |glotto=lemo1243 |glottorefname=Lemolang }}
'''Lemolang''' (self-designation: '''Limola''') is an [[Austronesian languages|Austronesian language]] of [[Sulawesi]], [[Indonesia]]. It is spoken in two villages in [[North Luwu Regency]], [[South Sulawesi]].
