{{infobox Organization |name = Radio Club de Chile |image = RCCH_logo.png |image_border = |size = 200px |caption = |map = |msize = |mcaption = |abbreviation = RCCH |motto = |formation = 1922<ref name="rcch"/> |extinction = |type = [[Non-profit organization]] |status = |purpose = Advocacy, Education |headquarters = |location = [[Santiago, Chile|Santiago]], [[Chile]] |region_served = [[Chile]] |membership = |language = [[Spanish language|Spanish]] |leader_title = President |leader_name = Galdino Besomi Sani CE3PG |main_organ = |affiliations = [[International Amateur Radio Union]] |num_staff = |budget = |website = http://www.ce3aa.cl/ |remarks = }}
The '''Radio Club de Chile''' ('''RCCH''') is a national [[non-profit organization]] for [[amateur radio]] enthusiasts in [[Chile]]. Key membership benefits of RCCH include the sponsorship of [[amateur radio operating award]]s and radio [[contesting|contests]], and a [[QSL card|QSL]] bureau for those members who regularly communicate with [[amateur radio operator]]s in other countries. RCCH represents the interests of Chilean amateur radio operators before Chilean and international telecommunications regulatory authorities.<ref name="rcch">Radio Club de Chile (2008). [http://www.ce3aa.cl/ Radio Club de Chile] official web site. Retrieved Aug. 15, 2008.</ref> RCCH is the national member society representing Chile in the [[International Amateur Radio Union]].<ref name="iaru">International Amateur Radio Union (2008). [http://www.iaru.org/iaru-soc.html "Member Societies"]. Retrieved Aug. 1, 2008.</ref>
